                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.397,
                                "byte_start": 87123,
                                "byte_stop": 112723,
                                "text": "I have the opinion of the Court to announce in Butterworth against Smith."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 6.397,
                                "stop": 21.248,
                                "byte_start": 112723,
                                "byte_stop": 172178,
                                "text": "In this case, the respondent, Michael Smith, was a reporter who obtained information relevant to alleged improprieties committed by the State Attorney\u2019s office in the Sheriff\u2019s Department in the Charlotte County, Florida."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.248,
                                "stop": 27.299,
                                "byte_start": 172178,
                                "byte_stop": 196419,
                                "text": "It was then called before a special grand jury which had been convened to investigate the allegation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.299,
                                "stop": 48.2,
                                "byte_start": 196419,
                                "byte_stop": 280011,
                                "text": "At the time he testified, he was warned by Florida officials not to reveal his testimony in any manner since he could be found criminally liable for violating a Florida law which prohibits a grand jury witness from ever disclosing the content, gist, or import of testimony given before that body."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.2,
                                "stop": 67.034,
                                "byte_start": 280011,
                                "byte_stop": 355348,
                                "text": "After the investigation ended, Smith set out to publish a news story about the subject matter of the investigation and he sued the State of Florida seeking a declaration that the Florida law, which I have mentioned, violated the First Amendment to the United States Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.034,
                                "stop": 81.164,
                                "byte_start": 355348,
                                "byte_stop": 411877,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit held that this Florida law was unconstitutional to the extent that it prohibits a witness from speaking about his testimony after a grand jury investigation has terminated."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.164,
                                "stop": 105.452,
                                "byte_start": 411877,
                                "byte_stop": 508948,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to review this judgment and for reasons stated in an opinion filed with the Clerk, we agree with the Court of Appeals that Florida\u2019s interest in prohibiting a grand jury witness from disclosing his own testimony after an investigation has ended are insufficient to overcome Smith\u2019s First Amendment right to make a truthful statement of information he acquired outside the grand jury room."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.452,
                                "stop": 108.638,
                                "byte_start": 508948,
                                "byte_stop": 521696,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.638,
                                "stop": 110.756,
                                "byte_start": 521696,
                                "byte_stop": 530160,
                                "text": "The decision of the Court is unanimous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.756,
                                "stop": 113.345,
                                "byte_start": 530160,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a concurring opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
